cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Cross-domain SOC validation dataset (v1, 2026-05-13)"
abstract: >
  A frozen, multi-domain benchmark for self-organized criticality (SOC) and
  related universality-class validation. Bundles 16 independently-fetched
  empirical systems (earthquakes, S&P 500 returns, DeFi liquidations, neural
  avalanches, wildfires, solar flares, bank failures, GitHub stars, power-grid
  disturbances, Wikipedia pageviews, Hawkes-Omori synthetics, lake regime
  shifts, traffic hysteresis, SIR contagion, tail-copula, plus a 7-system
  universal-collapse composite) with their canonical Clauset-Shalizi-Newman
  power-law fits, Omori temporal decays where applicable, and per-system
  arXiv-style companion paper drafts. Includes 4 synthetic null controls
  (Gaussian walk, exponential, Poisson inter-arrival, Poisson-Omori stack)
  that the same pipeline correctly rejects, a 35-class universality-class
  taxonomy with B1 (single-Opus) and B3 (3-DeepSeek ensemble) critic
  verdicts, the frozen pipeline source (~1.4k LoC of fitting + LLM guardrail
  + ensemble critic), and a 17-test sanity test suite. Suitable for cross-
  domain SOC validation, pipeline reproducibility benchmarking, and LLM
  ensemble-critic methodology research.
